originalText.text:
Gorgeous venue (held at the Holy Apostles Church)  but if you're here for a five hour open bar be warned that there are only 2 toilets for each gender.

I came here for the theSet's Winter Wonderland: 2015 New Years Eve with my friends. All 12 of us purchased through Pulsd and thought the $50 pricing was fantastic for the 5hr open bar and 1 hour buffet and ball drop champagne toast.

CONS
1. The guy in charge of the door was INCREDIBLY rude. When I asked him a question regarding the voucher he smiled and closed the door in my face. Turned out that if you purchased individual vouchers you didn't have to wait for the entire party to enter. I waited outside for over 45 minutes... in the cold.

2. 1 hour food buffet? Lies - don't call it a buffet if it's only 3 trays of food. I waited on line for half an hour to only get a cupcake because it all ran out.

3. "5 hour open bar" another lie - the bar was dry by the 3rd hour.

4. Champagne toast was all gone within 10 minutes of the ball drop.

5. There were only two bathroom stalls for each gender. This "open bar" event had 300+ people attend... you would think we'd need more bathrooms. Wait time for bathrooms ranged from 30-45 minutes and women resorted to invading the men's room.

6. The coat check lost track of people's jackets and everything was handled haphazardly.

7. One of the "professional" photographers there was very creepy and inappropriate.

PROS
It was for a good cause.

Bottom-line - My friends and I had a pretty disappointing night here and wouldn't come back for the venue (because of the bathroom situation) or any event hosted by The Set NYC
